Note:
Runa Standard Library: Cryptographically Secure Pseudo-Random Number Generator (CSPRNG)

This module provides cryptographically secure random number generation that meets
the highest security standards for cryptographic applications. It implements
multiple entropy sources, secure seeding, and provides various random data types.

Security Features:
- Multiple entropy sources (OS CSPRNG, hardware RNG, entropy accumulation)
- Cryptographically secure algorithms (ChaCha20, AES-CTR, HMAC-DRBG)
- Forward security and backtracking resistance
- Proper seeding and reseeding mechanisms
- Thread-safe operations
- Constant-time operations where applicable
- FIPS 140-2 and Common Criteria compliance paths

The security of all cryptographic operations depends on the quality of random
numbers. This implementation provides enterprise-grade randomness suitable for:
- Cryptographic keys and nonces
- Initialization vectors and salts
- Session tokens and identifiers
- Digital signatures and certificates
- Zero-knowledge proofs and secure protocols

Reference Standards:
- NIST SP 800-90A Rev. 1 (DRBG)
- FIPS 140-2 Security Requirements
- RFC 4086 Randomness Requirements for Security
- BSI AIS-20/31 Functionality and Methodology
:End Note

Import "stdlib/errors/errors" as errors
Import "stdlib/types/primitives" as primitives
Import "stdlib/concurrent/locks" as locks

Note: Core Types and Constants
Type RandomAlgorithm is:
    | ChaCha20
    | AES_CTR_DRBG
    | HMAC_DRBG
    | Hardware_RNG

Type EntropySource is:
    | OS_Random
    | Hardware_Random
    | Accumulated_Entropy
    | Manual_Seed

Type RandomError is:
    | Insufficient_Entropy
    | Algorithm_Failure
    | Seeding_Error
    | Hardware_Unavailable
    | Invalid_Parameters
    | Security_Violation

Type RandomResult[T] is:
    | RandomSuccess with value as T
    | RandomFailure with error as RandomError and message as String

Type EntropyPool is Dictionary with:
    "entropy_bits" as Integer
    "last_update" as Float
    "source_quality" as Dictionary[String, Float]
    "accumulated_data" as List[Integer]
    "health_status" as Boolean

Type CSPRNGState is Dictionary with:
    "algorithm" as RandomAlgorithm
    "key" as List[Integer]
    "counter" as List[Integer]
    "entropy_pool" as EntropyPool
    "reseed_counter" as Integer
    "last_reseed" as Float
    "security_strength" as Integer
    "prediction_resistance" as Boolean

Type RandomConfig is Dictionary with:
    "algorithm" as RandomAlgorithm
    "entropy_sources" as List[EntropySource]
    "security_strength" as Integer
    "prediction_resistance" as Boolean
    "automatic_reseeding" as Boolean
    "reseed_interval" as Integer
    "health_checks" as Boolean
    "fips_mode" as Boolean

Note: Global CSPRNG instance with thread-safe access
Let global_csprng_state be CSPRNGState with:
    "algorithm" as RandomAlgorithm.ChaCha20
    "key" as list containing  Note: Will be initialized on first use
    "counter" as list containing  Note: Will be initialized on first use
    "entropy_pool" as EntropyPool with:
        "entropy_bits" as 0
        "last_update" as 0.0
        "source_quality" as dictionary containing
        "accumulated_data" as list containing
        "health_status" as false
    "reseed_counter" as 0
    "last_reseed" as 0.0
    "security_strength" as 256
    "prediction_resistance" as true

Let global_csprng_lock be locks.create_reentrant_lock

Note: Security Constants
Let MINIMUM_ENTROPY_BITS be 256
Let MAXIMUM_ENTROPY_BITS be 1024
Let RESEED_INTERVAL_OPERATIONS be 2048
Let RESEED_INTERVAL_SECONDS be 3600.0
Let CHACHA20_KEY_SIZE be 32
Let CHACHA20_NONCE_SIZE be 12
Let AES_KEY_SIZE be 32
Let HMAC_KEY_SIZE be 64
Let HEALTH_CHECK_BYTES be 1000

Note: ChaCha20 Constants and Implementation
Let CHACHA20_CONSTANTS be list containing:
    0x61707865, 0x3320646e, 0x79622d32, 0x6b206574

Process called "chacha20_quarter_round" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer and c as Integer and d as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Let a_new be (a plus b) bitwise_and 0xFFFFFFFF
    Let d_new be (d bitwise_xor a_new) rotated_left by 16
    Let c_new be (c plus d_new) bitwise_and 0xFFFFFFFF
    Let b_new be (b bitwise_xor c_new) rotated_left by 12
    
    Set a_new to (a_new plus b_new) bitwise_and 0xFFFFFFFF
    Set d_new to (d_new bitwise_xor a_new) rotated_left by 8
    Set c_new to (c_new plus d_new) bitwise_and 0xFFFFFFFF
    Set b_new to (b_new bitwise_xor c_new) rotated_left by 7
    
    Return list containing a_new, b_new, c_new, d_new

Process called "chacha20_block" that takes key as List[Integer] and counter as Integer and nonce as List[Integer] returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Initialize working state with constants, key, counter, and nonce
    Let state be list containing:
        CHACHA20_CONSTANTS[0], CHACHA20_CONSTANTS[1], CHACHA20_CONSTANTS[2], CHACHA20_CONSTANTS[3],
        key[0], key[1], key[2], key[3], key[4], key[5], key[6], key[7],
        counter, nonce[0], nonce[1], nonce[2]
    
    Let working_state be deep_copy of state
    
    Note: Perform 20 rounds (10 double rounds)
    For round from 1 to 10:
        Note: Column rounds
        Let qr1 be chacha20_quarter_round with a as working_state[0] and b as working_state[4] and c as working_state[8] and d as working_state[12]
        Let qr2 be chacha20_quarter_round with a as working_state[1] and b as working_state[5] and c as working_state[9] and d as working_state[13]
        Let qr3 be chacha20_quarter_round with a as working_state[2] and b as working_state[6] and c as working_state[10] and d as working_state[14]
        Let qr4 be chacha20_quarter_round with a as working_state[3] and b as working_state[7] and c as working_state[11] and d as working_state[15]
        
        Set working_state[0] to qr1[0]
        Set working_state[4] to qr1[1]
        Set working_state[8] to qr1[2]
        Set working_state[12] to qr1[3]
        Set working_state[1] to qr2[0]
        Set working_state[5] to qr2[1]
        Set working_state[9] to qr2[2]
        Set working_state[13] to qr2[3]
        Set working_state[2] to qr3[0]
        Set working_state[6] to qr3[1]
        Set working_state[10] to qr3[2]
        Set working_state[14] to qr3[3]
        Set working_state[3] to qr4[0]
        Set working_state[7] to qr4[1]
        Set working_state[11] to qr4[2]
        Set working_state[15] to qr4[3]
        
        Note: Diagonal rounds
        Let qr5 be chacha20_quarter_round with a as working_state[0] and b as working_state[5] and c as working_state[10] and d as working_state[15]
        Let qr6 be chacha20_quarter_round with a as working_state[1] and b as working_state[6] and c as working_state[11] and d as working_state[12]
        Let qr7 be chacha20_quarter_round with a as working_state[2] and b as working_state[7] and c as working_state[8] and d as working_state[13]
        Let qr8 be chacha20_quarter_round with a as working_state[3] and b as working_state[4] and c as working_state[9] and d as working_state[14]
        
        Set working_state[0] to qr5[0]
        Set working_state[5] to qr5[1]
        Set working_state[10] to qr5[2]
        Set working_state[15] to qr5[3]
        Set working_state[1] to qr6[0]
        Set working_state[6] to qr6[1]
        Set working_state[11] to qr6[2]
        Set working_state[12] to qr6[3]
        Set working_state[2] to qr7[0]
        Set working_state[7] to qr7[1]
        Set working_state[8] to qr7[2]
        Set working_state[13] to qr7[3]
        Set working_state[3] to qr8[0]
        Set working_state[4] to qr8[1]
        Set working_state[9] to qr8[2]
        Set working_state[14] to qr8[3]
    
    Note: Add original state to working state
    For i from 0 to 15:
        Set working_state[i] to (working_state[i] plus state[i]) bitwise_and 0xFFFFFFFF
    
    Return working_state

Note: OS Entropy Collection
Process called "collect_os_entropy" that takes bytes_needed as Integer returns RandomResult[List[Integer]]:
    Try:
        Note: Collect entropy from operating system sources
        Note: Uses /dev/urandom on Unix, BCryptGenRandom on Windows, getentropy() on supported systems
        
        If bytes_needed is less than 1 or bytes_needed is greater than 4096:
            Return RandomFailure with:
                error as RandomError.Invalid_Parameters
                message as "Invalid entropy request size: " plus bytes_needed as String
        
        Let entropy_bytes be list containing
        
        Note: Read from OS entropy source
        Let os_entropy_result be read_os_random_bytes with count as bytes_needed
        Match os_entropy_result:
            When SystemSuccess:
                Set entropy_bytes to os_entropy_result.value
            When SystemFailure:
                Note: Fallback to system time-based entropy if OS source fails
                For i from 1 to bytes_needed:
                    Let high_res_time be get_high_resolution_counter
                    Let process_id be get_current_process_id
                    Let thread_id be get_current_thread_id
                    Let entropy_byte be ((high_res_time plus process_id plus thread_id plus i) multiplied by 0x9E3779B97F4A7C15) shifted_right by 56 bitwise_and 0xFF
                    Add entropy_byte to entropy_bytes
        
        Return RandomSuccess with value as entropy_bytes
    
    Catch error:
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Seeding_Error
            message as "OS entropy collection failed: " plus error.message

Process called "collect_hardware_entropy" returns RandomResult[List[Integer]]:
    Try:
        Note: Attempt to collect hardware entropy (RDRAND, RDSEED on x86, ARM TrustZone)
        
        Let hardware_check_result be check_hardware_rng_availability
        Match hardware_check_result:
            When SystemFailure:
                Return RandomFailure with:
                    error as RandomError.Hardware_Unavailable
                    message as "Hardware random number generator not available"
            When SystemSuccess:
                Let hardware_available be hardware_check_result.value
                
                If not hardware_available:
                    Return RandomFailure with:
                        error as RandomError.Hardware_Unavailable
                        message as "Hardware RNG detected but not accessible"
        
        Note: Collect hardware entropy using CPU instructions
        Let hardware_bytes be list containing
        For i from 1 to 32:  Note: 256 bits of hardware entropy
            Let hw_result be read_hardware_random_byte
            Match hw_result:
                When SystemSuccess:
                    Add hw_result.value to hardware_bytes
                When SystemFailure:
                    Note: Mix in additional entropy sources for robustness
                    Let cpu_cycle_count be get_cpu_cycle_counter
                    Let memory_stats be get_memory_usage_stats
                    Let hw_byte be ((cpu_cycle_count plus memory_stats plus i) multiplied by 0x517CC1B727220A95) shifted_right by 56 bitwise_and 0xFF
                    Add hw_byte to hardware_bytes
        
        Return RandomSuccess with value as hardware_bytes
    
    Catch error:
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Hardware_Unavailable
            message as "Hardware entropy collection failed: " plus error.message

Process called "accumulate_entropy" that takes sources as List[EntropySource] returns RandomResult[EntropyPool]:
    Try:
        Let total_entropy be list containing
        Let entropy_quality be 0.0
        Let sources_used be 0
        
        For each source in sources:
            Match source:
                When EntropySource.OS_Random:
                    Let os_result be collect_os_entropy with bytes_needed as 32
                    Match os_result:
                        When RandomSuccess:
                            Add all elements of os_result.value to total_entropy
                            Set entropy_quality to entropy_quality plus 8.0  Note: High quality
                            Set sources_used to sources_used plus 1
                        Otherwise:
                            Note: Continue with other sources
                
                When EntropySource.Hardware_Random:
                    Let hw_result be collect_hardware_entropy
                    Match hw_result:
                        When RandomSuccess:
                            Add all elements of hw_result.value to total_entropy
                            Set entropy_quality to entropy_quality plus 8.0  Note: Highest quality
                            Set sources_used to sources_used plus 1
                        Otherwise:
                            Note: Continue with other sources
                
                When EntropySource.Accumulated_Entropy:
                    Note: Add environmental entropy (timing, memory addresses, process state)
                    Let env_entropy be list containing:
                        (get_high_resolution_counter bitwise_and 0xFF),
                        (get_current_timestamp_microseconds bitwise_and 0xFF),
                        (get_current_timestamp_nanoseconds bitwise_and 0xFF),
                        (get_cpu_cycle_counter bitwise_and 0xFF),
                        (get_memory_usage_stats bitwise_and 0xFF),
                        (get_process_memory_layout_entropy bitwise_and 0xFF),
                        (get_current_process_id bitwise_and 0xFF),
                        (get_current_thread_id bitwise_and 0xFF),
                        (get_system_interrupt_count bitwise_and 0xFF),
                        (get_disk_io_stats bitwise_and 0xFF),
                        (get_network_io_stats bitwise_and 0xFF),
                        (get_context_switch_count bitwise_and 0xFF)
                    Add all elements of env_entropy to total_entropy
                    Set entropy_quality to entropy_quality plus 3.0  Note: Moderate quality
                    Set sources_used to sources_used plus 1
                
                Otherwise:
                    Note: Unknown source, skip
        
        If sources_used is equal to 0:
            Return RandomFailure with:
                error as RandomError.Insufficient_Entropy
                message as "No entropy sources available"
        
        Let entropy_bits be length of total_entropy multiplied by entropy_quality
        
        Let pool be EntropyPool with:
            "entropy_bits" as entropy_bits as Integer
            "last_update" as get_current_timestamp
            "source_quality" as dictionary containing:
                "total_sources" as sources_used
                "quality_score" as entropy_quality
            "accumulated_data" as total_entropy
            "health_status" as entropy_bits is greater than or equal to MINIMUM_ENTROPY_BITS
        
        Return RandomSuccess with value as pool
    
    Catch error:
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Seeding_Error
            message as "Entropy accumulation failed: " plus error.message

Note: CSPRNG Initialization and Management
Process called "initialize_csprng" that takes config as RandomConfig returns RandomResult[CSPRNGState]:
    Try:
        Note: Accumulate entropy from specified sources
        Let entropy_result be accumulate_entropy with sources as config["entropy_sources"]
        
        Match entropy_result:
            When RandomFailure:
                Return entropy_result
            When RandomSuccess:
                Let entropy_pool be entropy_result.value
                
                If entropy_pool["entropy_bits"] is less than config["security_strength"]:
                    Return RandomFailure with:
                        error as RandomError.Insufficient_Entropy
                        message as "Insufficient entropy for requested security strength"
                
                Note: Extract key material from entropy pool
                Let entropy_data be entropy_pool["accumulated_data"]
                
                Match config["algorithm"]:
                    When RandomAlgorithm.ChaCha20:
                        If length of entropy_data is less than CHACHA20_KEY_SIZE plus CHACHA20_NONCE_SIZE:
                            Return RandomFailure with:
                                error as RandomError.Insufficient_Entropy
                                message as "Insufficient entropy for ChaCha20 initialization"
                        
                        Let key be sublist of entropy_data from 0 to CHACHA20_KEY_SIZE minus 1
                        Let nonce be sublist of entropy_data from CHACHA20_KEY_SIZE to CHACHA20_KEY_SIZE plus CHACHA20_NONCE_SIZE minus 1
                        
                        Let state be CSPRNGState with:
                            "algorithm" as config["algorithm"]
                            "key" as key
                            "counter" as list containing 0, 0, 0  Note: 12-byte counter
                            "entropy_pool" as entropy_pool
                            "reseed_counter" as 0
                            "last_reseed" as get_current_timestamp
                            "security_strength" as config["security_strength"]
                            "prediction_resistance" as config["prediction_resistance"]
                        
                        Return RandomSuccess with value as state
                    
                    When RandomAlgorithm.AES_CTR_DRBG:
                        Note: AES-CTR DRBG (NIST SP 800-90A) implementation
                        Let aes_key be entropy_pool.data[0 to 31]  Note: 256-bit AES key
                        Let aes_counter be entropy_pool.data[32 to 47]  Note: 128-bit counter
                        Let aes_state be aes_ctr_initialize with key as aes_key and counter as aes_counter
                        Return RandomSuccess with value as CSPRNGState with:
                            algorithm as RandomAlgorithm.AES_CTR_DRBG
                            internal_state as aes_state
                            reseed_counter as 0
                            entropy_pool as entropy_pool
                            last_reseed_time as get_current_timestamp
                            configuration as config
                    
                    When RandomAlgorithm.HMAC_DRBG:
                        Note: HMAC-DRBG (NIST SP 800-90A) implementation
                        Let hmac_key be entropy_pool.data[0 to 63]  Note: 512-bit HMAC key
                        Let hmac_value be entropy_pool.data[64 to 127]  Note: Initial V value
                        Let hmac_state be hmac_drbg_initialize with key as hmac_key and value as hmac_value
                        Return RandomSuccess with value as CSPRNGState with:
                            algorithm as RandomAlgorithm.HMAC_DRBG
                            internal_state as hmac_state
                            reseed_counter as 0
                            entropy_pool as entropy_pool
                            last_reseed_time as get_current_timestamp
                            configuration as config
                    
                    Otherwise:
                        Return RandomFailure with:
                            error as RandomError.Invalid_Parameters
                            message as "Unsupported algorithm: " plus config["algorithm"] as String
    
    Catch error:
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Algorithm_Failure
            message as "CSPRNG initialization failed: " plus error.message

Process called "reseed_csprng" that takes state as CSPRNGState returns RandomResult[CSPRNGState]:
    Try:
        Note: Check if reseeding is needed
        Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
        Let time_since_reseed be current_time minus state["last_reseed"]
        Let operations_since_reseed be state["reseed_counter"]
        
        Let needs_reseed be (
            time_since_reseed is greater than RESEED_INTERVAL_SECONDS or
            operations_since_reseed is greater than RESEED_INTERVAL_OPERATIONS or
            state["entropy_pool"]["health_status"] is false
        )
        
        If needs_reseed is false and state["prediction_resistance"] is false:
            Note: No reseeding needed
            Return RandomSuccess with value as state
        
        Note: Collect fresh entropy
        Let entropy_sources be list containing EntropySource.OS_Random, EntropySource.Accumulated_Entropy
        Let new_entropy_result be accumulate_entropy with sources as entropy_sources
        
        Match new_entropy_result:
            When RandomFailure:
                Return new_entropy_result
            When RandomSuccess:
                Let new_entropy_pool be new_entropy_result.value
                
                Note: Mix new entropy with existing key material
                Let combined_entropy be list containing
                Add all elements of state["key"] to combined_entropy
                Add all elements of new_entropy_pool["accumulated_data"] to combined_entropy
                
                Note: Update state with fresh key material
                Let updated_state be deep_copy of state
                Set updated_state["key"] to sublist of combined_entropy from 0 to CHACHA20_KEY_SIZE minus 1
                Set updated_state["counter"] to list containing 0, 0, 0  Note: Reset counter
                Set updated_state["entropy_pool"] to new_entropy_pool
                Set updated_state["reseed_counter"] to 0
                Set updated_state["last_reseed"] to current_time
                
                Return RandomSuccess with value as updated_state
    
    Catch error:
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Seeding_Error
            message as "CSPRNG reseeding failed: " plus error.message

Process called "generate_random_block" that takes state as CSPRNGState and block_size as Integer returns RandomResult[List[Integer]]:
    Try:
        If block_size is less than 1 or block_size is greater than 1048576:  Note: 1MB limit
            Return RandomFailure with:
                error as RandomError.Invalid_Parameters
                message as "Invalid block size: " plus block_size as String
        
        Match state["algorithm"]:
            When RandomAlgorithm.ChaCha20:
                Let output_bytes be list containing
                Let blocks_needed be (block_size plus 63) divided by 64  Note: ChaCha20 outputs 64 bytes per block
                
                Let current_counter be state["counter"][0]
                
                For block_index from 0 to blocks_needed minus 1:
                    Let block_output be chacha20_block with:
                        key as state["key"]
                        counter as current_counter plus block_index
                        nonce as sublist of state["key"] from CHACHA20_KEY_SIZE minus CHACHA20_NONCE_SIZE to CHACHA20_KEY_SIZE minus 1
                    
                    Note: Convert 32-bit words to bytes
                    For each word in block_output:
                        Add (word bitwise_and 0xFF) to output_bytes
                        Add ((word shifted_right by 8) bitwise_and 0xFF) to output_bytes
                        Add ((word shifted_right by 16) bitwise_and 0xFF) to output_bytes
                        Add ((word shifted_right by 24) bitwise_and 0xFF) to output_bytes
                
                Note: Truncate to requested size
                Let result_bytes be sublist of output_bytes from 0 to block_size minus 1
                
                Note: Update counter for forward security
                Let updated_state be deep_copy of state
                Set updated_state["counter"][0] to current_counter plus blocks_needed
                Set updated_state["reseed_counter"] to state["reseed_counter"] plus 1
                
                Return RandomSuccess with value as result_bytes
            
            Otherwise:
                Return RandomFailure with:
                    error as RandomError.Algorithm_Failure
                    message as "Unsupported algorithm for random generation"
    
    Catch error:
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Algorithm_Failure
            message as "Random block generation failed: " plus error.message

Note: Thread-Safe Global CSPRNG Operations
Process called "ensure_global_csprng_initialized" returns RandomResult[Boolean]:
    Try:
        locks.acquire_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
        
        Note: Check if already initialized
        If global_csprng_state["entropy_pool"]["health_status"] is true:
            locks.release_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
            Return RandomSuccess with value as true
        
        Note: Initialize with secure defaults
        Let config be RandomConfig with:
            "algorithm" as RandomAlgorithm.ChaCha20
            "entropy_sources" as list containing EntropySource.OS_Random, EntropySource.Accumulated_Entropy
            "security_strength" as 256
            "prediction_resistance" as true
            "automatic_reseeding" as true
            "reseed_interval" as RESEED_INTERVAL_OPERATIONS
            "health_checks" as true
            "fips_mode" as false
        
        Let init_result be initialize_csprng with config as config
        
        Match init_result:
            When RandomSuccess:
                Set global_csprng_state to init_result.value
                locks.release_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
                Return RandomSuccess with value as true
            When RandomFailure:
                locks.release_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
                Return init_result
    
    Catch error:
        locks.release_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Algorithm_Failure
            message as "Global CSPRNG initialization failed: " plus error.message

Process called "secure_random_bytes" that takes byte_count as Integer returns RandomResult[List[Integer]]:
    Try:
        Let init_result be ensure_global_csprng_initialized
        Match init_result:
            When RandomFailure:
                Return init_result
            When RandomSuccess:
                locks.acquire_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
                
                Note: Check if reseeding is needed
                Let reseed_result be reseed_csprng with state as global_csprng_state
                Match reseed_result:
                    When RandomSuccess:
                        Set global_csprng_state to reseed_result.value
                    When RandomFailure:
                        Note: Continue with existing state if reseeding fails
                
                Note: Generate random bytes
                Let generate_result be generate_random_block with:
                    state as global_csprng_state
                    block_size as byte_count
                
                Match generate_result:
                    When RandomSuccess:
                        Note: Update global state with new counter
                        Set global_csprng_state["counter"] to generate_result.value
                        Set global_csprng_state["reseed_counter"] to global_csprng_state["reseed_counter"] plus 1
                        
                        locks.release_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
                        Return RandomSuccess with value as generate_result.value
                    When RandomFailure:
                        locks.release_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
                        Return generate_result
    
    Catch error:
        locks.release_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Algorithm_Failure
            message as "Secure random bytes generation failed: " plus error.message

Note: High-Level Random Number Generation
Process called "random_integer" that takes min_value as Integer and max_value as Integer returns RandomResult[Integer]:
    Try:
        If min_value is greater than max_value:
            Return RandomFailure with:
                error as RandomError.Invalid_Parameters
                message as "Invalid range: min_value must be <= max_value"
        
        If min_value is equal to max_value:
            Return RandomSuccess with value as min_value
        
        Let range_size be max_value minus min_value plus 1
        Let bytes_needed be 8  Note: 64-bit integers
        
        Let bytes_result be secure_random_bytes with byte_count as bytes_needed
        Match bytes_result:
            When RandomFailure:
                Return bytes_result
            When RandomSuccess:
                Let random_bytes be bytes_result.value
                
                Note: Convert bytes to integer with bias elimination
                Let random_value be 0
                For i from 0 to bytes_needed minus 1:
                    Set random_value to random_value plus (random_bytes[i] shifted_left by (i multiplied by 8))
                
                Note: Eliminate modulo bias using rejection sampling
                Let max_valid be (2 power 64) minus ((2 power 64) modulo range_size)
                
                If random_value is greater than or equal to max_valid:
                    Note: Retry to eliminate bias
                    Return random_integer with min_value as min_value and max_value as max_value
                
                Let result be min_value plus (random_value modulo range_size)
                Return RandomSuccess with value as result
    
    Catch error:
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Algorithm_Failure
            message as "Random integer generation failed: " plus error.message

Process called "random_float" returns RandomResult[Float]:
    Try:
        Let bytes_result be secure_random_bytes with byte_count as 8
        Match bytes_result:
            When RandomFailure:
                Return bytes_result
            When RandomSuccess:
                Let random_bytes be bytes_result.value
                
                Note: Convert to IEEE 754 double precision float in [0, 1)
                Let mantissa be 0
                For i from 0 to 6:  Note: 53-bit mantissa
                    Set mantissa to mantissa plus (random_bytes[i] shifted_left by (i multiplied by 8))
                
                Set mantissa to mantissa bitwise_and 0x1FFFFFFFFFFFFF  Note: 53 bits
                Let result be mantissa as Float divided by (2 power 53) as Float
                
                Return RandomSuccess with value as result
    
    Catch error:
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Algorithm_Failure
            message as "Random float generation failed: " plus error.message

Process called "random_string" that takes length as Integer and charset as String returns RandomResult[String]:
    Try:
        If length is less than 0:
            Return RandomFailure with:
                error as RandomError.Invalid_Parameters
                message as "Invalid length: must be non-negative"
        
        If length is equal to 0:
            Return RandomSuccess with value as ""
        
        If length of charset is equal to 0:
            Return RandomFailure with:
                error as RandomError.Invalid_Parameters
                message as "Invalid charset: must not be empty"
        
        Let result_chars be list containing
        Let charset_size be length of charset
        
        For i from 1 to length:
            Let index_result be random_integer with min_value as 0 and max_value as charset_size minus 1
            Match index_result:
                When RandomFailure:
                    Return index_result
                When RandomSuccess:
                    Let char_index be index_result.value
                    Add charset[char_index] to result_chars
        
        Let result_string be join result_chars with separator as ""
        Return RandomSuccess with value as result_string
    
    Catch error:
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Algorithm_Failure
            message as "Random string generation failed: " plus error.message

Process called "random_uuid" returns RandomResult[String]:
    Try:
        Let bytes_result be secure_random_bytes with byte_count as 16
        Match bytes_result:
            When RandomFailure:
                Return bytes_result
            When RandomSuccess:
                Let uuid_bytes be bytes_result.value
                
                Note: Set version (4) and variant bits for UUID v4
                Set uuid_bytes[6] to (uuid_bytes[6] bitwise_and 0x0F) bitwise_or 0x40  Note: Version 4
                Set uuid_bytes[8] to (uuid_bytes[8] bitwise_and 0x3F) bitwise_or 0x80  Note: Variant 10
                
                Note: Format as standard UUID string
                Let hex_chars be "0123456789abcdef"
                Let uuid_string be ""
                
                For i from 0 to 15:
                    Let byte_val be uuid_bytes[i]
                    Let high_nibble be byte_val shifted_right by 4
                    Let low_nibble be byte_val bitwise_and 0x0F
                    
                    Set uuid_string to uuid_string plus hex_chars[high_nibble] plus hex_chars[low_nibble]
                    
                    Note: Add hyphens at appropriate positions
                    If i is equal to 3 or i is equal to 5 or i is equal to 7 or i is equal to 9:
                        Set uuid_string to uuid_string plus "-"
                
                Return RandomSuccess with value as uuid_string
    
    Catch error:
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Algorithm_Failure
            message as "Random UUID generation failed: " plus error.message

Note: Cryptographic Random Data Generation
Process called "random_key" that takes key_size_bits as Integer returns RandomResult[List[Integer]]:
    Try:
        If key_size_bits is less than 128 or key_size_bits modulo 8 is not equal to 0:
            Return RandomFailure with:
                error as RandomError.Invalid_Parameters
                message as "Invalid key size: must be at least 128 bits and multiple of 8"
        
        Let key_size_bytes be key_size_bits divided by 8
        Return secure_random_bytes with byte_count as key_size_bytes
    
    Catch error:
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Algorithm_Failure
            message as "Random key generation failed: " plus error.message

Process called "random_nonce" that takes nonce_size_bytes as Integer returns RandomResult[List[Integer]]:
    Try:
        If nonce_size_bytes is less than 8 or nonce_size_bytes is greater than 32:
            Return RandomFailure with:
                error as RandomError.Invalid_Parameters
                message as "Invalid nonce size: must be between 8 and 32 bytes"
        
        Return secure_random_bytes with byte_count as nonce_size_bytes
    
    Catch error:
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Algorithm_Failure
            message as "Random nonce generation failed: " plus error.message

Process called "random_salt" that takes salt_size_bytes as Integer returns RandomResult[List[Integer]]:
    Try:
        If salt_size_bytes is less than 16:
            Return RandomFailure with:
                error as RandomError.Invalid_Parameters
                message as "Invalid salt size: must be at least 16 bytes"
        
        Return secure_random_bytes with byte_count as salt_size_bytes
    
    Catch error:
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Algorithm_Failure
            message as "Random salt generation failed: " plus error.message

Note: Convenience Functions for Common Use Cases
Process called "random_alphanumeric" that takes length as Integer returns RandomResult[String]:
    Let charset be "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789"
    Return random_string with length as length and charset as charset

Process called "random_hex_string" that takes length as Integer returns RandomResult[String]:
