    Return random_string with length as length and charset as charset

Note: Security Testing and Health Checks
Process called "test_randomness_quality" that takes sample_size as Integer returns RandomResult[Dictionary]:
    Try:
        If sample_size is less than 1000:
            Return RandomFailure with:
                error as RandomError.Invalid_Parameters
                message as "Sample size too small for meaningful test"
        
        Let bytes_result be secure_random_bytes with byte_count as sample_size
        Match bytes_result:
            When RandomFailure:
                Return bytes_result
            When RandomSuccess:
                Let random_data be bytes_result.value
                
                Note: Perform basic statistical tests
                Let byte_frequencies be list containing
                For i from 0 to 255:
                    Add 0 to byte_frequencies
                
                For each byte_val in random_data:
                    Set byte_frequencies[byte_val] to byte_frequencies[byte_val] plus 1
                
                Note: Calculate chi-square test statistic
                Let expected_frequency be sample_size as Float divided by 256.0
                Let chi_square be 0.0
                
                For each frequency in byte_frequencies:
                    Let diff be frequency as Float minus expected_frequency
                    Set chi_square to chi_square plus ((diff multiplied by diff) divided by expected_frequency)
                
                Note: Calculate entropy estimate
                Let entropy be 0.0
                For each frequency in byte_frequencies:
                    If frequency is greater than 0:
                        Let probability be frequency as Float divided by sample_size as Float
                        Set entropy to entropy minus (probability multiplied by log_base_2 of probability)
                
                Let results be dictionary containing:
                    "sample_size" as sample_size
                    "chi_square_statistic" as chi_square
                    "entropy_estimate" as entropy
                    "max_entropy" as 8.0
                    "quality_score" as (entropy divided by 8.0) multiplied by 100.0
                    "passes_basic_tests" as (entropy is greater than 7.9 and chi_square is less than 293.248)  Note: 95% confidence
                
                Return RandomSuccess with value as results
    
    Catch error:
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Algorithm_Failure
            message as "Randomness quality test failed: " plus error.message

Note: Configuration and Management
Process called "get_csprng_status" returns Dictionary:
    locks.acquire_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
    
    Let status be dictionary containing:
        "algorithm" as global_csprng_state["algorithm"] as String
        "security_strength" as global_csprng_state["security_strength"]
        "prediction_resistance" as global_csprng_state["prediction_resistance"]
        "reseed_counter" as global_csprng_state["reseed_counter"]
        "last_reseed" as global_csprng_state["last_reseed"]
        "entropy_bits" as global_csprng_state["entropy_pool"]["entropy_bits"]
        "health_status" as global_csprng_state["entropy_pool"]["health_status"]
        "initialized" as global_csprng_state["entropy_pool"]["health_status"]
    
    locks.release_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
    Return status

Process called "force_reseed" returns RandomResult[Boolean]:
    Try:
        locks.acquire_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
        
        Let reseed_result be reseed_csprng with state as global_csprng_state
        Match reseed_result:
            When RandomSuccess:
                Set global_csprng_state to reseed_result.value
                locks.release_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
                Return RandomSuccess with value as true
            When RandomFailure:
                locks.release_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
                Return reseed_result
    
    Catch error:
        locks.release_lock with lock as global_csprng_lock
        Return RandomFailure with:
            error as RandomError.Seeding_Error
            message as "Forced reseed failed: " plus error.message

Note: Utility Functions for Constant-Time Operations
Process called "constant_time_compare" that takes a as List[Integer] and b as List[Integer] returns Boolean:
    If length of a is not equal to length of b:
        Return false
    
    Let result be 0
    For i from 0 to length of a minus 1:
        Set result to result bitwise_or (a[i] bitwise_xor b[i])
    
    Return result is equal to 0

Process called "secure_zero" that takes data as List[Integer] returns List[Integer]:
    Let zeroed_data be list containing
    For i from 1 to length of data:
        Add 0 to zeroed_data
    
    Return zeroed_data

Note: Helper Functions
Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Returns current Unix timestamp with microsecond precision
    Let seconds be get_system_time_seconds
    Let microseconds be get_system_time_microseconds
    Return seconds as Float plus (microseconds as Float divided by 1000000.0)

Process called "get_current_timestamp_microseconds" returns Integer:
    Note: Returns microseconds since epoch with high precision
    Let seconds be get_system_time_seconds
    Let microseconds be get_system_time_microseconds
    Return (seconds multiplied by 1000000) plus microseconds

Process called "get_current_timestamp_nanoseconds" returns Integer:
    Note: Returns nanoseconds since epoch using high-resolution counter
    Let high_res_counter be get_high_resolution_counter
    Let base_time_ns be get_system_time_seconds multiplied by 1000000000
    Let counter_offset_ns be (high_res_counter modulo 1000000000)
    Return base_time_ns plus counter_offset_ns

Process called "deep_copy" that takes data as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Note: Production-grade recursive deep copy with circular reference detection
    Let copied_dict be dictionary containing
    Let visited_objects be dictionary containing  Note: Track visited objects for circular reference detection
    Let object_id_counter be 0
    
    Process called "deep_copy_recursive" that takes obj as Any and visited as Dictionary returns Any:
        Note: Get object identity hash for circular reference detection
        Let obj_id be generate_object_id with object as obj
        
        If visited contains key obj_id:
            Note: Circular reference detected, return placeholder
            Return dictionary containing "__circular_ref__" as obj_id
        
        Set visited[obj_id] to True
        
        Match type of obj:
            When "Dictionary":
                Let result_dict be dictionary containing
                For each key in keys of obj:
                    Let copied_key be deep_copy_recursive with obj as key and visited as visited
                    Let copied_value be deep_copy_recursive with obj as obj[key] and visited as visited
                    Set result_dict[copied_key] to copied_value
                Remove key obj_id from visited
                Return result_dict
            
            When "List":
                Let result_list be list containing
                For each item in obj:
                    Let copied_item be deep_copy_recursive with obj as item and visited as visited
                    Add copied_item to result_list
                Remove key obj_id from visited
                Return result_list
            
            When "String":
                Remove key obj_id from visited
                Return obj  Note: Strings are immutable
            
            When "Integer":
                Remove key obj_id from visited
                Return obj  Note: Integers are immutable
            
            When "Float":
                Remove key obj_id from visited
                Return obj  Note: Floats are immutable
            
            When "Boolean":
                Remove key obj_id from visited
                Return obj  Note: Booleans are immutable
            
            Otherwise:
                Note: Complex object - create new instance and copy fields
                Let result_obj be create_new_instance with type as type of obj
                Let fields be get_object_fields with object as obj
                For each field_name in fields:
                    Let field_value be get_field_value with object as obj and field as field_name
                    Let copied_field be deep_copy_recursive with obj as field_value and visited as visited
                    Set field on result_obj with name as field_name and value as copied_field
                Remove key obj_id from visited
                Return result_obj
    
    Return deep_copy_recursive with obj as data and visited as visited_objects

Process called "get_process_memory_layout_entropy" returns Integer:
    Note: Extracts entropy from process memory layout (ASLR)
    Let stack_address be get_stack_pointer_address
    Let heap_address be get_heap_base_address
    Let code_address be get_code_segment_address
    Let entropy_value be (stack_address bitwise_xor heap_address bitwise_xor code_address)
    Return entropy_value bitwise_and 0xFFFFFFFF

Process called "log_base_2" that takes x as Float returns Float:
    Note: Calculates logarithm base 2 using natural log
    If x is less than or equal to 0.0:
        Return 0.0  Note: Invalid input
    
    Let ln_x be natural_logarithm of x
    Let ln_2 be natural_logarithm of 2.0
    Return ln_x divided by ln_2

Note: System Interface Functions - Platform-specific implementations
Type SystemResult[T] is:
    | SystemSuccess with value as T
    | SystemFailure with error as String

Process called "read_os_random_bytes" that takes count as Integer returns SystemResult[List[Integer]]:
    Note: Platform-specific OS entropy collection using pure Runa
    Note: Unix: /dev/urandom, Linux: getrandom(), Windows: BCryptGenRandom, macOS: getentropy()
    Try:
        Note: Use essential runtime call for random bytes
        Return system_call_random_bytes with count as count
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback: use accumulated entropy pool
        Return accumulate_entropy_bytes with count as count

Process called "check_hardware_rng_availability" returns SystemResult[Boolean]:
    Note: Check for hardware RNG support (RDRAND/RDSEED on x86, RNDR on ARM)
    Let has_rdrand be cpu_feature_check with feature as "RDRAND"
    Let has_rdseed be cpu_feature_check with feature as "RDSEED" 
    Let has_arm_rndr be cpu_feature_check with feature as "RNDR"
    Return SystemSuccess with value as (has_rdrand or has_rdseed or has_arm_rndr)

Process called "read_hardware_random_byte" returns SystemResult[Integer]:
    Note: Execute hardware RNG instruction (RDRAND/RDSEED/RNDR)
    Let hw_byte_result be hardware_random_instruction
    Return hw_byte_result

Process called "get_system_time_seconds" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current time in seconds since Unix epoch using pure Runa
    Try:
        Note: Use essential runtime call for time
        Let time_seconds be system_call_time_current
        Return time_seconds as Integer
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback: use high-resolution time
        Let time_ns be system_call_time_high_res
        Return (time_ns as Integer) divided by 1000000000

Process called "get_system_time_microseconds" returns Integer:
    Note: Get microsecond component of current time using pure Runa
    Try:
        Note: Use essential runtime call for time
        Let time_seconds be system_call_time_current
        Let microseconds be (time_seconds minus (time_seconds as Integer)) multiplied by 1000000.0
        Return microseconds as Integer
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback: use high-resolution time
        Let time_ns be system_call_time_high_res
        Return (time_ns as Integer) modulo 1000000

Process called "get_high_resolution_counter" returns Integer:
    Note: Get high-resolution performance counter using pure Runa
    Try:
        Note: Use essential runtime call for high-resolution time
        Return system_call_time_high_res
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback: use current time multiplied by large factor
        Let time_seconds be system_call_time_current
        Return (time_seconds multiplied by 1000000000.0) as Integer

Process called "get_cpu_cycle_counter" returns Integer:
    Note: Read CPU cycle counter (RDTSC on x86, CNTVCT_EL0 on ARM64)
    Let cycle_result be cpu_cycle_count_instruction
    Return cycle_result

Process called "get_current_process_id" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current process ID using pure Runa
    Try:
        Note: Use essential runtime call for process information
        Let process_info be system_call_process_get_info
        Return process_info.pid
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback: use time-based pseudo PID
        Let time_seconds be system_call_time_current
        Return (time_seconds as Integer) modulo 65536

Process called "get_current_thread_id" returns Integer:
    Note: Get current thread ID using pure Runa
    Try:
        Note: Use essential runtime call for process information
        Let process_info be system_call_process_get_info
        Return process_info.tid
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback: use time-based pseudo TID
        Let time_ns be system_call_time_high_res
        Return (time_ns as Integer) modulo 65536

Process called "get_memory_usage_stats" returns Integer:
    Note: Get memory usage statistics for entropy using pure Runa
    Try:
        Note: Use essential runtime call for memory information
        Let memory_info be system_call_memory_get_info
        Return memory_info.usage_bytes
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback: use time-based pseudo memory usage
        Let time_ns be system_call_time_high_res
        Return (time_ns as Integer) modulo 1048576

Process called "get_stack_pointer_address" returns Integer:
